exrest: The Enquirer-Gazette is a weekly newspaper published in Upper Marlboro, Maryland. It was founded on January 30, 1925, when Frederick Sasscer, Jr. and his partner Samuel A. Wyvill purchased the Marlboro Gazette from Mary and Charles Wilson, combining it with the paper they previously owned, the Prince George's Enquirer and Southern Maryland Advertiser. Sasscer remained editor of the Enquirer-Gazette until his death in 1929.
